<br>
It's amazing how homosexuality gets linked to roleplaying in an attempt to denegrate both in the powergamer's discourse.  I've noticed that very few self-identified roleplayers say that powergaming is &quot;gay&quot;.  On the contrary, roleplayers and roleplaying are called &quot;gay&quot; (or &quot;ghey&quot;) with a certain amount of frequency.  While my personal response, IC &amp; OOC, is &quot;Yeah, I'm gay, what's your point?&quot;, it does reveal something about the anxieties of those attempting to make that link. <p>"These discourses of heterosexuality oppress us in the sense that they prevent us from speaking unless we speak in their terms."<BR>
-Monique Wittig, "The Straight Mind"<BR>
