<br>
One thing that I have noticed, however, is that the people you do run across tend to be better players, or maybe just kinder players.  I wonder how much that has to do with the fact that FV is a roleplaying server or because there are so few people that we are less likely to burn bridges with the few others we come across.<br>
<br>
I had been playing on E'ci, but the overcrowding was starting to get annoying.  The standard newbie leveling zones were packed (yes, I played a lot of twinks).  40 people in Oasis, competing for things to kill.  50 people in Lake of Ill Omen.  People LFG all over the place.  On Firiona Vie, my experience has been that you rarely find enough people in a single zone to form a full group (and 95% of them are /anon or /role), and that's assuming you ignore level restrictions.  And now you want to make it even harder to group?  No thanks.<br>
