<br>
Alignment even in the PnP games was never intended as a law of nature, but as a consequence of character.  Your characters history (including race) determined initial alignment and if your subsequent actions deviated, a good DM would adjust your alignment, perhaps with severe consequences, such as your now misaligned diety getting pissed off at you.  Alignment should be an indicator of character behavior, not a hard-coded racial prejudice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 703<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/19/02 4:45:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2563.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alignment should be ..</span><hr size=1> I like the idea of using XP-bonuses &amp; penalties to encourage/discourage certain groupings.  This seems to me to address the requests of both those who think we should have alignments and those who think people should be free to roleplay however they want.<br>
