F=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tremayne>Tremayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 12:09:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2563.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alignment should be ..</span><hr size=1> &lt;Alignment should be faction based and xp-enforced. If you work your faction up with the home city of the race you want to group with, you have no penalties or even a bonus. You could even tie gaining and loosing faction into grouping and earning xp; eg. group with a troll, gain grobb faction, loose faction just about everwhere else (ie. become more troll-like in your factions).&gt;<br>
<br>
I had a similar idea of just putting PC's on the same faction system as NPC's. Your 'personal' faction would be set by your home city/class combination (i.e. Necro from Neriak = The Dead, Necro from Ak'Anon = Dark Reflection, and so on). When you group, there would be a check against the other members of the group as to their standing with your faction (and vice-versa). Enforcement would be by faction bonus/penalty based on individual standing, so that amiable/indiff./apprehensive gets no adjustment, dubious and lower gets a penalty, kindly and up gets a bonus. This would be more realistic than being based on an arbitrary alignment, as would the effect on reputation (faction) be more realistic than an XP penalty. Linked to this would be other changes: /con would have to work PC-to-PC, so you can tell someone else's faction standing with your own; Making all or nearly all races startable in every city for those RP situations (like, say, a Ogre raised by Humans) where starting faction would be 'non-standard'. There would have to be limits on the faction hit as well, like one hit per login per character (the faction check happens once and isn't checked again as long as you're logged in.) It's something to think about, anyway... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 1:07:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2563.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alignment should be ..</span><hr size=1> Nice idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucobra102.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cobra102</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 7:52:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2563.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alignment should be ..</span><hr size=1> Actually it is a very nice idea and closer to a &quot;realistic&quot; situation. It would however drive a coach and horses through the existing faction system around which much of the game is built. <br>
<br>
Instead of my human cleric having to do strange quests to penetrate an enemy city, all he has to do is group with it's residents a while, and then group with his own kind again to restore it. In a way this is I suppose exactly what he would do, earn the trust of the enemy to infiltrate their city and then he must re-earn the trust of his own kind or remain suspect. It makes a deal more sense than giving stacks of wine to an NPC.<br>
<br>
It would require major changes to the game engine. It would have to be weighted for group composition and duration. It will never be done because the population of FV does not justify such a re-write. Good Idea though.<br>
<br>
On re-instating the old alignment rules I think it is too late to turn back the clock.<br>
<br>
From an RP perspective much of the best fantasy is based on rebels, renegades and exiles who forsake their own origins in search of a different destiny. It is much more interesting than the race-hatred stereotypes which (if I may say it here) reinforce intolerance both in EQ and RL.<br>
<br>
I mean think of the books that would never have been written if Alignment rules had been imposed in Fantasy Literature.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 9:51:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2563.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alignment should be ..</span><hr size=1> The original alignment restrictions were a bit silly to begin with. The idea that evil is evil, good is good and neutral is whatever was just an arbitrary drawing of the line. Not all evils are created equal. Racial or diety restrictions would have been more approriate to a RP server. Does that eliminate or make the end game more challenging? Yes, but it would have preserved the integrity of the socalled RP server. It would have kept the current plague of blue server rejects from overrunning this server to get to their ::cough:: achievements ::cough:: in the end game. <br>
<br>
VI sold you out from the start by not setting concrete rules. They caved in completely on May 8 when they announced you could RP any way you want. Yeh, just like on the other servers! Anyway it's too late to close the door now. It would not be fair to the RP NOT ONLY NOT PREFERRED BUT NOT ACCEPTED players to suddenly find they couldn't play together. <p><CENTER>

